author: Sammy Batten - staff writer
title: College football: Thursday's in-state games
text:
College football: Thursday's in-state games By Sammy Batten - staff writer 
Georgia Southern (5-1, 3-0) at Appalachian State (5-1, 2-0) 
Time: 7:30 p.m. TV: ESPNU 
The bulletin board: This is a showdown between two of the top contenders for the Sun Belt title. ... Georgia Southern beat Appalachian State, 34-14, a year ago before the Mountaineers finished with a six-game winning streak. ... Appalachian has won 10 of its last 11 games. ... Sophomore quarterback Taylor Lamb passed for 261 yards and ran for 103 for the Mountaineers in Saturday’s rout of Louisiana-Monroe. ... Georgia Southern’s Matt Breida has rushed for 900 yards and 11 touchdowns. 
Temple (6-0, 3-0) at East Carolina (4-3, 2-1) 
Time: 7 p.m. TV: ESPN2 
The bulletin board: It’s a battle between the first-place team in the AAC’s East Division, Temple, and second-place ECU. ... The Owls debuted at No. 22 in The Associated Press Top 25 this week. ... Josh Hawkins returned an interception 100 yards to spark ECU’s rout of Tulsa last Saturday. ... Montese Overton leads the Pirates and is second in the AAC with seven quarterback sacks. ... Temple leads the AAC in scoring defense (14.7) and total defense (295.5).
